#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:6
msgid "Using camera sensor drivers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:8
msgid ""
"This section describes common practices for how the V4L2 sub-device "
"interface is used to control the camera sensor drivers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:11
msgid "You may also find :ref:`media_writing_camera_sensor_drivers` useful."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:14
msgid "Frame size"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:16
msgid ""
"There are two distinct ways to configure the frame size produced by camera "
"sensors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:20
msgid "Freely configurable camera sensor drivers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:22
msgid ""
"Freely configurable camera sensor drivers expose the device's internal "
"processing pipeline as one or more sub-devices with different cropping and "
"scaling configurations. The output size of the device is the result of a "
"series of cropping and scaling operations from the device's pixel array's "
"size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:27
msgid "An example of such a driver is the CCS driver."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:30
msgid "Register list based drivers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:32
msgid ""
"Register list based drivers generally, instead of able to configure the "
"device they control based on user requests, are limited to a number of "
"preset configurations that combine a number of different parameters that on "
"hardware level are independent. How a driver picks such configuration is "
"based on the format set on a source pad at the end of the device's internal "
"pipeline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:38
msgid "Most sensor drivers are implemented this way."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:41
msgid "Frame interval configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:43
msgid ""
"There are two different methods for obtaining possibilities for different "
"frame intervals as well as configuring the frame interval. Which one to "
"implement depends on the type of the device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:48
msgid "Raw camera sensors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:50
msgid ""
"Instead of a high level parameter such as frame interval, the frame interval "
"is a result of the configuration of a number of camera sensor implementation "
"specific parameters. Luckily, these parameters tend to be the same for more "
"or less all modern raw camera sensors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:55
msgid "The frame interval is calculated using the following equation::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:60
msgid ""
"The formula is bus independent and is applicable for raw timing parameters "
"on large variety of devices beyond camera sensors. Devices that have no "
"analogue crop, use the full source image size, i.e. pixel array size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:64
msgid ""
"Horizontal and vertical blanking are specified by ``V4L2_CID_HBLANK`` and "
"``V4L2_CID_VBLANK``, respectively. The unit of the ``V4L2_CID_HBLANK`` "
"control is pixels and the unit of the ``V4L2_CID_VBLANK`` is lines. The "
"pixel rate in the sensor's **pixel array** is specified by "
"``V4L2_CID_PIXEL_RATE`` in the same sub-device. The unit of that control is "
"pixels per second."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:70
msgid ""
"Register list based drivers need to implement read-only sub-device nodes for "
"the purpose. Devices that are not register list based need these to "
"configure the device's internal processing pipeline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:74
msgid ""
"The first entity in the linear pipeline is the pixel array. The pixel array "
"may be followed by other entities that are there to allow configuring "
"binning, skipping, scaling or digital crop, see :ref:"
"`VIDIOC_SUBDEV_G_SELECTION <VIDIOC_SUBDEV_G_SELECTION>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:80
msgid "USB cameras etc. devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:82
msgid ""
"USB video class hardware, as well as many cameras offering a similar higher "
"level interface natively, generally use the concept of frame interval (or "
"frame rate) on device level in firmware or hardware. This means lower level "
"controls implemented by raw cameras may not be used on uAPI (or even kAPI) "
"to control the frame interval on these devices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:89
msgid "Rotation, orientation and flipping"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:91
msgid ""
"Some systems have the camera sensor mounted upside down compared to its "
"natural mounting rotation. In such cases, drivers shall expose the "
"information to userspace with the :ref:`V4L2_CID_CAMERA_SENSOR_ROTATION "
"<v4l2-camera-sensor-rotation>` control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:96
msgid ""
"Sensor drivers shall also report the sensor's mounting orientation with the :"
"ref:`V4L2_CID_CAMERA_SENSOR_ORIENTATION <v4l2-camera-sensor-orientation>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/camera-sensor.rst:99
msgid ""
"Sensor drivers that have any vertical or horizontal flips embedded in the "
"register programming sequences shall initialize the :ref:`V4L2_CID_HFLIP "
"<v4l2-cid-hflip>` and :ref:`V4L2_CID_VFLIP <v4l2-cid-vflip>` controls with "
"the values programmed by the register sequences. The default values of these "
"controls shall be 0 (disabled). Especially these controls shall not be "
"inverted, independently of the sensor's mounting rotation."
msgstr ""
